    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect SIMD data access in dft864 and dft288 functions\n\n### Summary\nThe dft864 and dft288 functions in the PHY DFT library were incorrectly accessing SIMD registers instead of individual complex numbers when reorganizing input data for sub-transforms. This caused incorrect FFT results due to data misalignment.\n\nAdditionally, the scaling loops were iterating 4 times more than necessary, processing garbage data beyond the actual FFT output.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Fixed input data reorganization in dft864() and dft288() to properly access individual complex numbers\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Corrected scaling loop bounds from N to N/4 for proper SIMD register count\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call dft864() with any input data\n2. Observe incorrect output due to:\n   - Input data being read from wrong SIMD register indices\n   - Scaling operation processing 4x more data than intended\n3. Compare with reference FFT implementation to see mismatched results\n\nThe incorrect behavior manifests as corrupted FFT output that does not match expected frequency domain representation.\n"
}